First Long Island Investors LLC Invests $4.83 Million in Allergan PLC. (AGN)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 26th, 2017 // No Comments 

First Long Island Investors LLC purchased a new position in shares of Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm purchased 20,200 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $4,826,000. 
Several other large investors also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. Camber Capital Management LLC acquired a new position in shares of Allergan PLC. during the fourth quarter worth $114,035,000. Norges Bank acquired a new position in shares of Allergan PLC. during the fourth quarter worth $682,333,000. WFG Advisors LP boosted its position in shares of Allergan PLC. by 6,726.1% in the fourth quarter. WFG Advisors LP now owns 47,100 shares of the company’s stock worth $215,000 after buying an additional 46,410 shares during the period. Appaloosa LP boosted its position in shares of Allergan PLC. by 249.8% in the fourth quarter. Appaloosa LP now owns 4,261,406 shares of the company’s stock worth $894,938,000 after buying an additional 3,043,097 shares during the period. Finally, Baupost Group LLC MA boosted its position in shares of Allergan PLC. by 71.5% in the fourth quarter. Baupost Group LLC MA now owns 3,432,603 shares of the company’s stock worth $720,881,000 after buying an additional 1,430,625 shares during the period. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 84.68% of the company’s stock. 




Shares of Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN) traded up 0.19% during trading on Wednesday, reaching $255.10. 576,046 shares of the company’s stock were exchanged. Allergan PLC. has a 52 week low of $184.50 and a 52 week high of $261.27. The company’s 50-day moving average is $241.06 and its 200 day moving average is $235.56. The stock has a market capitalization of $85.68 billion, a PE ratio of 7.95 and a beta of 1.16. Allergan PLC. also saw some unusual options trading on Monday. Traders purchased 8,807 call options on the company. This represents an increase of 160% compared to the average volume of 3,384 call options.


 Get Allergan PLC. alerts:



Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, May 9th. The company reported $3.35 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $3.32 by $0.03. The company had revenue of $3.57 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $3.53 billion. Allergan PLC. had a return on equity of 7.29% and a net margin of 82.42%. The firm’s quarterly revenue was up 5.1% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the business posted $3.04 earnings per share. On average, analysts forecast that Allergan PLC. will post $16.08 earnings per share for the current year. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY WARNING: This news story was first posted by BNB Daily and is the property of of BNB Daily. If you are accessing this news story on another site, it was copied illegally and reposted in violation of United States and international trademark & copyright laws. The legal version of this news story can be read at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/26/first-long-island-investors-llc-invests-4-83-million-in-allergan-plc-agn-updated.html. 
A number of research analysts recently weighed in on AGN shares. Deutsche Bank AG lifted their price objective on shares of Allergan PLC. from $262.00 to $265.00 and gave the company a “buy” rating in a report on Tuesday, March 28th. Royal Bank Of Canada set a $279.00 price objective on shares of Allergan PLC. and gave the company a “buy” rating in a report on Wednesday, April 12th. Citigroup Inc. restated a “focus list” rating and issued a $261.27 price objective (up previously from $184.50) on shares of Allergan PLC. in a report on Friday, April 21st. Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) cut shares of Allergan PLC. from a “buy” rating to a “neutral” rating and set a $262.00 price objective for the company. in a report on Wednesday, May 10th. Finally, UBS AG restated a “buy” rating and issued a $275.00 price objective on shares of Allergan PLC. in a report on Monday, May 15th. Seven research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and fifteen have issued a buy rating to the stock. The stock has an average rating of “Buy” and an average price target of $275.31.
In other Allergan PLC. news, Director Nesli Basgoz sold 1,889 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction on Thursday, May 18th. The stock was sold at an average price of $220.45, for a total value of $416,430.05. The transaction was disclosed in a legal filing with the SEC, which is available through this hyperlink. Company insiders own 0.36% of the company’s stock. 
Allergan PLC. Company Profile
Allergan, Inc is a multi-specialty healthcare company. The Company focuses on developing and commercializing pharmaceuticals, biologics, medical devices and over-the-counter (OTC) products. It discovers, develops and commercializes a range of products for the ophthalmic, neurological, medical aesthetics, medical dermatology, breast aesthetics, urological and other specialty markets. 

 
